55.9	Ashram	Ashram	Traditionally, an ashram (Sanskrit/Hindi: आश्रम) is a spiritual hermitage. Additionally, today the term ashram often denotes a locus of Indian cultural activity such as yoga, music study or religious instruction, the moral equivalent of a studio or dojo.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Ashrams_on_the_banks_of_Ganges%2C_Rishikesh.jpg/200px-Ashrams_on_the_banks_of_Ganges%2C_Rishikesh.jpg
